-- Italy’s CDP to Use $20 Billion to Back Economy, Messaggero Says
-- B y   C h i a r a   R e m o n d i n i
-- 2012-04-22T10:05:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/italy-s-cdp-to-use-20-billion-to-back-economy-messaggero-says.html
Italy’s state-owned lender Cassa
Depositi e Prestiti SpA plans to use 15 billion euros ($20
billion) to 16 billion euros this year to help counter a credit
crunch and support the “real economy,” Chairman Franco Bassanini told daily  il Messaggero .  “We will continue to make long-term investments to finance
businesses, infrastructure and local administrations,”
Bassanini was cited as saying in the interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
